raw_data.title: CAD / Design
raw_data.description: CAD/Design is responsible for looking at all drawings and specifications sheet and applying our scope of work within the drawing. They are also responsible for all technical documentation as the job progresses, especially where all wire/cable was run and the terminations that were made. In addition, they make the technical drawings for equipment housing, cabling, splices, interior runs, exterior runs, network labeling, and any other items that need to be drafted. At the end of a job or project they are responsible for completing all documentation of work completed that we hand over to our clients.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Bachelor's or an additional 10 years experience

labor_categories.years_experience: Bachelor's or an additional 10 years experience

raw_data.title: Field Technician
raw_data.description: Field technicians are considered subject matter experts and have the highest level of technical training. They innovate and lead the entire team as the project progresses. They establish all cable connections including NVR, data, cameras, alarm pane ls, door contacts, motion detectors, cellular communicators, intrusion panels, access control panels, power supplies, card readers, electronic locking hardware, and electric by running, pulling, terminating, and splicing wires. They also install and integrate all networking equipment such as routers and switches. In addition, they are responsible for testing and troubleshooting all connections. Senior technicians report to the field technician.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Bachelor's or an additional 10 years experience

labor_categories.years_experience: Bachelor's or an additional 10 years experience

raw_data.title: Jr. Cable Technician
raw_data.description: Junior Cable Technicians are able to do all the functions of a Senior Cable Technician however they do not have the authority and decision making power. They are responsible for assisting in cable connections including NVR, data, cameras, alarm panels, door contacts, motion detectors, cellular communicators, intrusion panels, access control panels, power supplies, card readers, electronic locking hardware, and electric by running, pulling, terminating, and splicing wires. They also install and integrate all networking equipment such as routers and switches. They are also equipped to do general laborer type work such as construction of walls, ceiling, and floors. In addition, they are responsible for testing and troubleshooting all connections. They must report to a senior to verify the work that they do.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: High School Diplmoa equivalent or and additonal 5 years experince

labor_categories.years_experience: High School Diplmoa equivalent or and additonal 5 years experince

raw_data.title: Pre-Site Preparation
raw_data.description: Pre-Site Preparation is responsible for gathering initial requirements and specifications and going to the field or job site and figuring out the best possible scenarios to conduct work. They are responsible for   getting the permits and dig tickets, if any, as well as all licenses that may be needed. In addition, the presite preparation crew insures all material and supplies are ordered and available for the work crew to be able to start without any delays. Pre-Site Preparation is also responsible for insuring cleanup and restoration of any areas that may have been affected while work was being conducted.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Bachelor's or an additional 10 years experience

labor_categories.years_experience: Bachelor's or an additional 10 years experience

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: The Project Manager helps the team understand the vision for the project as well as the benefits to the organization. They also are in charge of covering the scope, schedule, and tracking of the project as it progresses. The project manager is actively engaging team members and providing feedback on a daily or weekly basis. They are also responsible for reporting the status of the project to all stakeholders involved.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Bachelor's or an additional 10 years experience

raw_data.title: Sr. Cable Technician
raw_data.description: Senior Cable Technicians plan and execute the installation of wiring and equipment. They are required to follow all technical specifications, requirements, diagrams, and schedules. They establish all cable connections including NVR, data, cameras, alarm panels, door contacts, motion detectors, cellular communicators, intrusion panels, access control panels, power supplies, card readers, electronic locking hardware, and electric by running, pulling, terminating, and splicing wires. They also install and integrate all networking equipment such as routers and switches. They are also equipped to do general laborer type work such as construction of walls, ceiling, and floors. In addition, they are responsible for testing and troubleshooting all connections. Senior technicians are in charge of all Junior Technicians on the job.
